  "texts": [
    "We will proceed in this section assuming familiarity with that material.",
    "For the purposes of possibility semantics, it is more convenient to take the multiplicative operators ■ i as the primitive operators of the BAO, rather than the additive operators ♦ i, which we define by♦ i x:= -■ i -x.For a BAO A = ⟨A, ∧, -, ⊤, {■ i } i∈I ⟩, let ⟨A, ≤⟩ be the associated Boolean lattice, with x ≤ y iff x ∧ y = x.",
    "We will focus on the following classes of BAOs, with labels from Litak 2005a.Definition 5.1 (Classes of BAOs).",
    "Let A = ⟨A, ∧, -, ⊤, {■ i } i∈I ⟩ be a nontrivial BAO.",
    "2.A is an A-BAO iff ⟨A, ≤⟩ is an atomic lattice as in Definition 4.13;3."
  ],
